ZH: 路的弯曲会让你迷失方向。
EN: The bends in the road will make you lose your way.

ZH: 弯曲的树枝挡住了我们的去路。
EN: The bent branches blocked our path.

ZH: 绕过这个湖的弯处，就可以看到美丽的风景了。
EN: After going around the bend of this lake, you can see beautiful scenery.

ZH: 弯曲的河流和周围的绿树构成了一幅美丽画面。
EN: The winding river and the surrounding green trees form a beautiful picture.

ZH: 我的腿弯了，站不稳了。
EN: My legs are bent and I can't stand firm.

ZH: 不要弯曲你的脊柱，会伤到自己的健康。
EN: Don't bend your spine, it will hurt your health.

ZH: 他弯了腰捡起了地上的东西。
EN: He bent down to pick up the things on the ground.

ZH: 她那弯细的眉毛总是很吸引人。
EN: Her curved eyebrows are always very attractive.

ZH: 这座桥有许多弯道要小心驾驶。
EN: This bridge has many bends that require careful driving.

ZH: 动物园里有一条弯曲的小径，有很多有趣的动物。
EN: There is a winding path in the zoo, with many interesting animals.

ZH: 弯曲的河流中游着一群野鸭。
EN: A group of wild ducks swim in the winding river.

ZH: 汽车在弯道上飞驰而过。
EN: The car sped past on the bend.

ZH: 骑车时请注意弯道。
EN: Please pay attention to the bends while riding a bike.

ZH: 弯曲的山路需要小心驾驶。
EN: The winding mountain road requires careful driving.

ZH: 舞台上的女演员弯着身子跳舞。
EN: The actress on the stage danced with a bent body.

ZH: 宝宝刚学会走路，经常摔倒在弯曲的楼梯上。
EN: The baby just learned to walk, often falling on the bent stairs.

ZH: 弯弯的小船漂浮在湖面上。
EN: The curved boat floats on the lake.

ZH: 他弯起了嘴角，露出了微笑。
EN: He bent up the corners of his mouth, showing a smile.

ZH: 弯弯的彩虹挂在天空上。
EN: The curved rainbow hangs in the sky.

ZH: 请勿在弯道超车，以免出现危险。
EN: Please do not overtake on the bends to avoid danger.
